---
/**
 * LangDemo - a working miniature of bloggydoggy.com's reader-controlled
 * language modes, for the case study. Same mechanism as the blog's
 * LanguageSelector + T pair (every mode in the DOM, stacked in one grid cell,
 * toggled by class), but self-contained: no localStorage, no site-wide event
 * bus. It broadcasts `bd-demo:lang` on document so the quiz demo further down
 * the page can follow it, which is exactly how the real blog behaves.
 *
 * The paragraph is a real excerpt from the blog's rice-planting post, all
 * three modes as published.
 */
---

<figure class="lang-demo" data-lang="en">
  <div class="ld-controls" role="group" aria-label="Reading language">
    <button type="button" data-ld-btn="en" class="ld-pill is-active" aria-pressed="true">English</button>
    <button type="button" data-ld-btn="en_simple" class="ld-pill" aria-pressed="false">Ez English</button>
    <button type="button" data-ld-btn="ja" class="ld-pill" aria-pressed="false">日本語</button>
  </div>

  <div class="ld-stage">
    <p class="ld-text" data-ld-text="en" lang="en">
      Recently I went and planted rice with Japanese 5th graders at the
      countryside elementary school where I work. It was an amazing experience
      that I will never forget, and today I would like to share it with you.
    </p>
    <p class="ld-text is-hidden" data-ld-text="en_simple" lang="en">
      I planted rice with Japanese 5th graders! I work at their school. It was
      so much fun. I want to tell you about it!
    </p>
    <p class="ld-text is-hidden" data-ld-text="ja" lang="ja">
      最近、私は、自分が働いている田舎の小学校で、日本の5年生たちと一緒にお米を植えてきました。それは一生忘れられない素晴らしい経験で、今日はそれを皆さんにお伝えしたいと思います。
    </p>
  </div>

  <figcaption>
    A real paragraph from the blog's rice-planting post, in all three published
    modes. The quiz further down follows this toggle too, same as on the blog.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.lang-demo').forEach((demo) => {
    const buttons = demo.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-ld-btn]');
    const texts = demo.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-ld-text]');

    const setLang = (lang: string) => {
      demo.dataset.lang = lang;
      texts.forEach((el) => {
        el.classList.toggle('is-hidden', el.dataset.ldText !== lang);
      });
      buttons.forEach((btn) => {
        const active = btn.dataset.ldBtn === lang;
        btn.classList.toggle('is-active', active);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(active));
      });
      document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('bd-demo:lang', { detail: { lang } }));
    };

    buttons.forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => setLang(btn.dataset.ldBtn ?? 'en'));
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .lang-demo { margin: 0; }

  .ld-controls {
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    padding: var(--space-1);
    background: var(--color-surface-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .ld-pill {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    background: none;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.85rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background var(--transition-base), color var(--transition-base);
  }
  .ld-pill:hover { color: var(--color-text); }
  .ld-pill.is-active {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent-contrast);
  }

  /* All three modes share one grid cell so the panel keeps the tallest height
     and nothing below it jumps when the language changes. */
  .ld-stage {
    display: grid;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-5);
  }
  .ld-text {
    grid-row: 1;
    grid-column: 1;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
    transition: opacity 0.15s ease-out;
  }
  .ld-text.is-hidden {
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }
</style>
